## Fast mode（默认速度）

**On by default** in this repo. User says **`god speed full`** or **`multitask`** to re-enable background subagents + thorough flow.

### Execution

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Foreground tools — direct read/grep/edit/shell | Background `Task` subagents for normal bugs/features |
| **Quick** → Cursor **solo** (label/typo/1-file format) | Claude `Task` for tiny Quick (hangs; 2026-07-22) |
| **Quick** spec triage (G1 still applies for new features) | Standard/Thorough unless user asks |
| Answer in one pass when possible | Split into parallel agents |
| `npm run build` only if JS/Vue/CSS changed | Build after every tiny edit |
| Browser verify only if user asks | Auto browser smoke |
| Visual bug fix: P1 data/HTML proof required; P2 crop optional (`07-bugfix-evidence-crop`) | Skip P1 on print/UI glyph bugs |
| Aikido scan only after substantive code diff | Scan on questions/docs-only |

**Conflict resolve:** fast mode + Claude Senior → **size gate wins**. Tiny = solo. Heavy = Task Claude (`08` / `12`).

### Session boot

- **`continue`** → skip reading `SESSION_STATE.md` / `progress.md` unless user said continue
- No OpenSpec boot unless coding task needs it

### Still apply

- `02-pl-seven-product-scope.mdc` — 7 Direct Book products only
- Minimal diff, no drive-by refactors, no commit unless asked
- `windows-herd-gitbash.mdc` for PHP commands

### Commands

| User says | Effect |
|-----------|--------|
| `fast mode` | Confirm fast mode (already default) |
| `god speed full` / `multitask` | Background subagents OK; read session handoff on continue |
| `thorough` | Full spec + verification pipeline |
